00:12:46.359 --> 00:12:48.479
How do you choose how they should interact?

00:12:49.159 --> 00:12:53.239
So hopefully I think this is not, you know, this is a book that's, you know,

00:12:53.239 --> 00:12:57.400
you've got to be fairly far along in your journey with R and data science,

00:12:57.400 --> 00:13:00.719
because now you're wanting to write bigger functions, but I think this is a

00:13:00.719 --> 00:13:05.520
pretty, this is sort of a gap in the current selection of R books, which

00:13:05.520 --> 00:13:10.239
compared to other programming languages, just have far fewer books on kind of

00:13:10.239 --> 00:13:14.039
like, you know, general programming topics like, like design.

